  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Video recording of ultrasound skills, rated by consultant radiologists.</measure>
    <time_frame>Ratings are to be completed within three months of performance.</time_frame>
    <description>The video-recordings of the technical performances are merged with the ultrasonography screen-recordings to one anonymized video-clip. These combined video-clips are rated with the OSAUS rating by two raters. The OSAUS scale (Objective Structured Assessment of Ultrasound Skills) is used for all performance assessments. The raters are consultant radiologists.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Cost-effectiveness of mobile app guided versus textbook guided training</measure>
    <time_frame>September 2016</time_frame>
  </primary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>Diagnostic accuracy</measure>
    <time_frame>On site via checklist, evaluated on average one day after performance.</time_frame>
    <description>Participants are given five videocases, to assess for eFAST verifiable pathology.</description>
  </secondary_outcome>
